The Minister of Youths and Sports, Mr Sunday Dare is currently inspecting the state of facilities at the Obafemi Awolowo (formerly Liberty) Stadium, Ibadan. The inspection comes as parts of the efforts of the Federal Government to get first hand information and know the state of the facility with the intention of upgrading for optimal use. Some of the facilities inspected so far includes the main bowl, the swimming pool, the hall among others. The Minister whose visit was unscheduled expresses delight at the enthusiasm of athletes and sportsmen and women training in various activities at the facility Details later